== Potato Wedges ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Place @butter{2%tbsp} in a #small bowl{} and bring to room temperature. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim and thinly slice @Button Mushrooms{4%ounce}. Halve @Potato Buns{2}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with @Olive Oil{2%tsp}, @Fry Seasoning{1%tsp}, and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. (You'll use the rest of the Fry Seasoning later.)

Roast on top rack until browned and crisp, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Dijonnaise ==

While potatoes roast, in a second small bowl, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @Sour Cream{2%tbsp}, and @Dijon Mustard{2%tsp}. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.

== Mushrooms and Patties ==

Melt @Butter{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and slightly crisp, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, combine @Ground Turkey{10%ounce}, @Garlic Powder{1/2%tsp}, remaining @Fry Seasoning{3%tsp}, @salt{3/4%tsp}, and pepper. Form mixture into two patties (four patties for 4), each slightly wider than a burger bun.

> TIP: Wet hands first to prevent sticking.

Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%tsp} in pan used for mushrooms over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Lower heat if patties begin to brown too quickly.

In the last 1-2 minutes of cooking, evenly top each patty with mushrooms and @Swiss Cheese{2%slices}; cover pan until cheese melts.

== Assembly ==

While patties cook, combine softened @Butter{3%tbsp} with remaining @Garlic Powder{1/2%tsp}. Spread garlic butter onto cut sides of buns.

Toast, cut sides up, on top rack of oven until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Spread bottom buns with as much Dijonnaise as you like. Fill buns with patties. Divide burgers and potato wedges between plates. Serve with any remaining Dijonnaise on the side.